column2: We had a personal visit- sunny
Cool- lake is cleaner than usual- and there is some algae.
Rainy week with weed cutting all week.
Cloudy- lake looks lousy.  The lake level is 95.65.  Water level: very low.
Very weedy.  Water level: very low.
Water very green and the weather is cloudy.  Water level: very low.
Lake is very weedy and low- lake level is 95.52.
Lake is very green.  Water level: very low.
Sunny- lake very green.  Water level: very low.
Cloudy and getting colder.  Water level: very low.
Last reading- getting cold- pulled boat out of the lake.  Water level: very low.
Removed 1/2 million tons of weeds and sprayed
Some green algae.  Water level: very low.
Very hot.  Water level: very low.
Very hot and humid.  Water level: very low.
Algae.  Water level: very very low
Assumed 12:00 noon time unknown.  Water level: very low.
Assumed 12:00 noon time unknown.  Water level: very low.
Assumed 12:00 noon time unknown.  Water level: very low.
Overcast- very calm- no waves- algae coating entire lake- heavier at S and W shores- thin at middle
Bright sun- slight wind- some algae
N- w- S shores green with algae- very bad in Kearley bay- especially the odor- color and smell stick to boat
Sunny- slight. wind- algae down- little fishing done- water low
Sunny- few weeds- slight algae- 2 days after storm- possibly milfoil near shore
Sunny- little wind- milfoil in Kearly bay- weeds near shores- 1" rain - high winds over weekend
Sunny- some waves- seems like weeds are dying
Partly cloudy- slight wind- weeds dying
Cloudy- the temperature is 80 degrees F- and rough water.  0.2" of rain from 7/19 to 7/19. monitored with bill Reitmeyer.
Sunny- few clouds- weeds dying- reducing clarity
Algae bloom- W shore bad- rest okay
Sunny- blue/green algae on w/southwest sides- weeds also
The temperature is 55 degrees- cloudy- and west wind. 6.85" of rain from 8/18-9/19.  Monitored with bill Reitmeyer.
Sunny- 72 F- algae on W shore
Mostly clear- still weed in Kearley bay. 1.25" of rain from 9/26-10/14.  Monitored with bill Reitmeyer.
Weeds thick along shoreline- 2.25" rain 6/1- water clearer than other years
Hot- calm- weedy- fishing slowed considerably
Clear- algae bloom- rain: 1.6" on 7/12-.1" on 7/3
Windy.  The rain gauge reading from 7/1-7/29 was 7.75 inches.
Week of strong winds (e at 10-20 mph).
Weeds are very heavy along some shores. milfoil is bad on west shore.
Weeds are thick in bays and along most shores.
Algae is bad along the shore- smells bad too!
Monitored with Otis Wendt.  Rain gauge reading from 7/1-7/31 is 2.31 inches.
Monitored with Otis Wendt.  Rain gauge reading from 8/1-8/31 is 1.77 inches. slight wind.
Monitored with Otis Wendt.  The rain gauge reading from 10/1-10/14 was 1.05 inches.
No algae- but weeds are sure growing.
Light NE wind- waves 3-4"- cloudy- very heavy boat traffic.
Never saw so many weeds around here before.
June rainfall 9.15"- much wind- trees down- homes damaged- one car totaled
Lake higher than ever seen before- water clarity suffered from storms.
Cold- some wind- rainfall for September is 2.68"
Clear- hot and windy- weedy along the shores.  Rain gauge reading from 5/1-5/31 was 1.1 inches.
Sunny- slight breeze- signs of algal blooms- ducks- weeds below the surface.  Rain gauge reading from 6/1-6/30 is 4.7 inches.
We got new sampler this year- algal blooms.  Rain gauge reading from 7/1-7/31 was 5.4 inches.
Sunshine- windy- algal blooms has turned the lake surface dark green along the shoreline.  Rain gauge reading from 8/1-8/31 is 4.9 inches.
Calm- cloudy- and 42 degrees- algal bloom- still evident.  The rain gauge reading from 9/1-9/30 is 3.6 inches. this concludes testing for 1994.
Algae starting to clear up.  This is the last report for this year.
Sunny- light wind- 75 degrees- some algae.
Sunny- hot- gentle breeze- algal blooms quite evident- plants are visible but only below the surface.
Lot of algae- sunny- windy- hot 90 degrees.
Cloudy- calm- 85 degrees- lots of algae.
Warm- cloudy- and severe algal blooms.
Sunny- calm- 85 degrees- lots of algae.
Sunny- calm- 75 degrees- lots of algae.
Clear- calm- 65 degrees- lots of algae.
Sunny- windy- 70 degrees- algal blooms prevalent.
Sunny- calm- 50 degrees- very little algae.
Cloudy- cold- 40 degrees- very little algae.  Last test of the year.
Sunny- partly cloudy- some lake weeds are coming- 65 degrees.
Sunny- calm- lots of weeds- 74 degrees.
Cloudy- light wind- lot of weeds- 65 degrees.
Sunny- light wind- 75 degrees. lot of weeds.
Sunny- light wind- weed ( ) down. 75 degrees.
Sunny- lot of algae- 70 degrees- nice day.
Sunny- calm- 70 degrees.  Algal blooms and weed growth are both abundant.
Sunny- light wind. lot of algae and weeds. 70 degrees.
Partly cloudy- light wind- lots of algae- 66 degrees.
Partly cloudy- light wind- lots of algae and weeds- 80 degrees.
Partly sunny- light wind- lots of algae- 65 degrees.
Sunny- no wind- lot of algae- 75 degrees.
Sunny- lot of algae. many boats- 80 degrees.
Cloudy- lots of algae- light wind- 60 degrees.
Algal blooms and plants are abundant.  Clear and calm-58 degrees.
Less algae- sunny- light wind- 60 degrees.
Sunny- windy- moderate algal bloom- ducks on the lake- weeds are on the bottom.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 3'.
Sunny- windy- clear- sun and windy.  70 degrees.
Sunny- light wind.  Lots of algae.  70 degrees.
Sunny- light wind- the temperature is 80 degrees- lots of algae and some weeds- rain gauge reading from 6/1-6/30 is five inches.
Cloudy.  75 degrees.  Lots of weeds in the water and algae.  Light winds.
Sunny- no wind.  Lots of algae.
Clear- no wind- lots of algae- rain gauge reading from 7/11-7/31 is 5.1 inches.
Cloudy- no wind.  65 degrees.  Lots of algae and a few weeds.
Cloudy- light wind.  60 degrees.  Lots of algae- some weeds.
Sunny- no wind- lots of algae and few weeds- rain gauge reading from 8/1-8/3 is 5.4 inches.
Lots of algae.  Sunny- 65 degrees.  No wind.
Calm- no wind- sunny- lots of algae- no weeds- the temperature is 65 degrees- rain gauge reading from 9/1-9/30 is 2.2 inches.
Clear and calm.  Algal blooms abundant.
Clear and calm.  Algal blooms abundant.
Cloudy and windy.  Minor algae bloom.
Sunny- calm- 49 F. recent heavy rains resulted in heavy soil erosion from farm fields.
Sunny. windy. abnormal heavy rains continue.
Partly cloudy- windy- 70 degrees. water has been abnormally green in May and june.
Sunny- calm. 70 degrees. water continues to be green and very murky.
Partly sunny- light winds- 80-84 degrees; 1" of rain during week
partly cloudy- winds SE at 10-15mph.  Mike Ross assisted in data collection. Destrat system started 5/14/2011 Increase of DO
clear ski- calm winds clear ski- calm winds
clear-breezy winds at about 10 miles per hour clear-breezy 10 mph winds  clear-10 mph winds
Clear-sunny-temperature 75- light winds-no rain for the past week. Saw two bald eagles over the lake
Cloudy- low winds. storms both days before measures. noticeable algae in the water. low amounts of weeds.
windy- sunny and no clouds- warm temperature.
very windy- cloudy- temperatures in the 60s
Sunny- Mild wind. Destrat emitter lines not cleaned as per Onterra.
Partly sunny. light chop. Destrat emitter lines not cleaned as per Onterra.

Lake light chop. After readings turned on Destrat after readings. Assessed weed conditions few weeds in only NW muskie bay and west of island- also fibrous algae along south shore from bait store to Welks. Matt Ross helped
Sunny- light chop. 3 out of 5 destrat lines running
1" of rain early morning. Sunny mild breeze. Found out had bad DO probe
Sunny- mild wind. Destrat not working
Replace DO probe cap. Sunny mild
Some blue Green Algae Beach Closed for Blue green Algae
